reviews.text:
Mixed this up, yet subbed VT Bilberry for FA Bilberry at 1%. I get one of two things going on here. Knowing what is inside this mix, I definitely taste the melon mix going on. (Honestly, I think that's a downfall with DIY in general, is that you know what is in the mix, so your brain pinpoints those flavors out) Which, if that's what this was supposed to be, you got my vote.&#xD;
Now, if you were to hand this to me, blindly, and just say 'Vape this!' I can totally see the grape aspect here. It seems as if you deskinned a red grape and just popped it in my mouth. There is a watery, yet textured aspect to it. A more natural of the vine grape than that bullshit purple candy grape.&#xD;
Either way you look at it, it's good.
